01/02/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH)-- The major parties in Bosnia and Herzegovina discussed Friday (30 January) terms for electing state defence minister by 15 February.
Barisa Colak, leader of the Croatian Democratic Union in BiH, said the party would agree to support a Bosniak or Serb candidate and called for a quick election procedure.
The parties stressed the defence minister will play an important role for the country's EU and NATO accession goals.
In other news, the Bosnian Serb government proclaimed Eid al-Adha as an official holiday for the Muslims of Republika Srpska.
For the first time, Bosnian Muslim workers would be able to take the holiday off.
(BBC, TV Hayat, AFP - 30/01/04)
